sqlite browser - db browser,

new database
sql1

Execute SQL
	CREATE TABLE Users(
	name VARCHAR(128),
	email VARCHAR(128)
	)

^^^ this is a contract
>>> execute SQL

128 characters

making the data model, be explicit about the data 

SQL insert
	insert statement inserts a row into a table

INSERT INTO Users (name, email) VALUES ('Kristin','kf@email.com')

DELETE FROM Users WHERE email='ted@email.com'

UPDATE Users SET name='Charles' WHERE email='csev@email.com'

Retrieving records: Select

SELECT*FROM Users
SELECT*FROM Users WHERE email='csev@email.com'

sorting with ORDER BY
	you can add an ORDER BY clause to SELECT statements to get the results sorted in ascending or descending order

SELECT*FROM Users ORDER BY email
SELECT*FROM Users ORDER BY name

